commit.message:
Where do I begin

SCSS Changes
Uses Native OS fonts (or not)
Removed OpenSans
Removed Unsued CSS Prefixes (`-o`, `-ms`, `-moz`, and ect)

Use zepto.js

Lot faster than jQuery and works well for a platform which only
needs Chromium functionality.

Ready for v0.0.3-alpha

After catching up to multiple Ion Updates (Including
the switch to SCSS for Ion Development), the app is stable and
ready to be deployed (or at least shared)

Upgraded to Electron 1.0

Also made changes for new Ion Schedule JS and CSS
Fix Bugs and Update Components + Dependencies

Switch to New Day Schedule Framework

This is a massive change, some things might not work yet

Changed from HTML Parsing to JSON

This should improve loading speeds and allow a more flexible UI

Add Key Codes

Press <kbd>Q</kbd> to Quit
Press <kbd>R</kbd> to Reload
Press <kbd>T</kbd> to load Today's Schedule
